          "ins_item_num": null,
          "ins_total": null,
          "f9": "The insurance report did not include a separate line item for universal starter course. We are requesting 344 LF of asphalt starter strip as a standalone line item. Starter strip is a distinct material from field shingles, serving a specific functional role at eave and rake edges that standard shingle pricing does not account for. Bundling starter into the shingle line item does not reflect the actual material cost or installation method, and separate estimating of starter is consistent with standard Xactimate practices. Please see the attached EagleView report confirming the perimeter measurements supporting this quantity.",
          "photo_anchor": "starter-strip",
          "sub_name": "",
          "ins_item_nums": [],
          "ins_qty": 0,
          "ins_carrier_notes": [
            "INS#3 (Laminated - comp. shingle rfg. - w/out felt): Age/Life: 10/30 yrs, Condition: Avg, DEP%: 33.33%. Auto Calculated Waste: 16.7%, 6.05SQ. Options: Valleys: Closed-cut (half laced), Include eave starter course: Yes, Include rake starter course: No, Exposure - Hip/Valley/Starter: 5 5/8\". Bundle Rounding: 0.8%, 0.29SQ (included in waste calculation above). This line item includes an allowance of $110.33 per unit, which reflects current market values in your area. Market prices were verified by Material Supply Warehouse (MSW). While you or your contractor are under no obligation to use this supplier, MSW allows you or your contractor of choice to have materials delivered to your home for installation. For more information on MSW, please visit www.materialsupplywarehouse.com, or contact them at info@materialsupplywarehouse.com, or 888-508-5009."
          ]
        },
